article.headline: Radford 78, Presbyterian 61
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Artsiom Parakhouski scored 21 points to lead Radford to a 78-61 win over Presbyterian on Saturday night. Parakhouski added eight rebounds for the Highlanders (13-10, 10-2 Big South Conference), who have won four straight games. Phillip Martin scored 16 points, and Amir Johnson added 15. Bryan Bostic scored 20 points of 8 of 17 shooting for the Blue Hose (10-13, 7-5). Al'Lonzo Coleman added 15 points and 12 rebounds. Presbyterian committed 21 turnovers, 13 of which were Radford steals. They also failed to record a blocked shot, while Radford had five. The Highlanders shot 49 percent from the field (25-for-51) and 88.9 percent from the free-throw line (24-for-27).
